# Git Workflow and Documentation History Rules

For every new feature, bug fix, test update, documentation update, or refactor, follow these rules.

## Branch Rules

- Do not make feature changes directly on main.
- Do not make feature changes directly on dev unless explicitly asked.
- Create a new descriptive branch before starting work.

Examples:
- feature/task-filter
- feature/dashboard-summary
- bugfix/dashboard-count
- docs/readme-update
- test/core-validation
- feature/stretch-activity-log

## Documentation History Rules

Whenever code changes are made, update all affected history/documentation files.

Update relevant files in:

- docs/
- project-notes/
- ai-prompts/
- tool-specific/cursor-workflow/

Never overwrite previous history. Always append new entries.

## Required History Updates

For every branch/task, record:

- Branch name
- Date
- Purpose of change
- Files created
- Files modified
- Database changes
- API changes
- Frontend changes
- Tests added or updated
- Cursor prompt summary
- What AI suggested
- What was accepted
- What was changed
- What was rejected
- Reason
- Suggested commit message

## Project Notes to Maintain

Update these when relevant:

- project-notes/project-memory.md
- project-notes/feature-log.md
- project-notes/decision-log.md
- project-notes/bug-log.md
- project-notes/api-log.md
- project-notes/database-log.md
- project-notes/frontend-components.md
- project-notes/testing-log.md

## Cursor Workflow Files to Maintain

Update these when relevant:

- tool-specific/cursor-workflow/project-context.md
- tool-specific/cursor-workflow/spec.md
- tool-specific/cursor-workflow/tasks.md
- tool-specific/cursor-workflow/cursor-rules-or-instructions.md

## AI Prompt History

Update the correct file under ai-prompts/.

Examples:
- Planning → ai-prompts/01-project-planning.md
- Backend → ai-prompts/02-backend-design.md
- Frontend → ai-prompts/03-frontend-ui.md
- Testing → ai-prompts/04-testing.md
- Debugging → ai-prompts/05-debugging.md
- Code review → ai-prompts/06-code-review.md
- Stretch feature → create a new numbered prompt file if needed
- Git workflow / process → ai-prompts/08-git-workflow-rules.md

## End of Task Summary

At the end of every task, provide:

1. Files created
2. Files modified
3. Database changes
4. API changes
5. Frontend changes
6. Tests added or updated
7. Documentation updated
8. Suggested commit message
9. Suggested branch name
10. Suggested PR description
11. Remaining tasks
12. Risks

Never leave documentation out of sync with code.
